"26:34:7" : {s: 26, a: 34, w: 7, r: "علم", t: "عَلِيمٌۭ", l: "عَلِيم", lc: 163, tl: "ʿalīmun", lb: "পরম জ্ঞানী",e: "learned", b: "মহাজ্ঞানী", i: "yang pandai", f: 100, rm: "to mark/sign/distinguish, creations/beings, world, science/learning/knowledge/information, aware/know. By means of which one knows a thing, hence it signifies world or creation, because by it the Creator is known. alim (pl. ulama) - one who is learned/wise or knows.", ag: "صفة نكرة", eg: "Adjective Indefinite state", tag: "ADJ", pos: "ADJ", att: "INDEF", qual: "NOM", deg: "", gen: "M", num: "S", mood: "", lu: "أَعْلَمُ،عَلِمَ،عَلِيمٌۢ"},
"26:35:1" : {s: 26, a: 35, w: 1, r: "رود", t: "يُرِيدُ", l: "أَرَادَ", lc: 139, tl: "yurīdu", lb: "ইচ্ছা করা",e: "He wants", b: "চান", i: "ia hendak", f: 38, rm: "to seek, ask a thing gently, search (for food), go to and fro in a pasture, go round about. iradatun - will, free will. mirwad - axle of a pully. rawada - to long after, desire, seduce, entice, seduce against the will (with an) as in 12:126. yuridu - he wishes, intends. It is used as an auxiliary verb as in 18:77. The word iradah is used for power and capacity with reference to subjugation as well as to option and choice. ruwaidan - for a little while, go gently (according to some grammarians the word is a diminutive form of which verbal noun is not in use, it is used as sing. plu. f. m.).", ag: "فعل مضارع صيغة ٤", eg: "Verb Imperfect 4th form", tag: "V", pos: "V", att: "IMPF", qual: "(IV)", deg: "3", gen: "M", num: "S", mood: "", lu: "أَرَادَ"},
"26:35:2" : {s: 26, a: 35, w: 2, r: "", t: "أَن", l: "أَن", lc: 577, tl: "an", lb: "যে, যেন",e: "to", b: "যেন/যে", i: "bahwa", f: 462, rm: "", ag: "حرف مصدري ", eg: "Subordinating conjunction ", tag: "SUB", pos: "SUB", att: "", qual: "", deg: "", gen: "", num: "", mood: "", lu: ""},
"26:35:3" : {s: 26, a: 35, w: 3, r: "خرج", t: "يُخْرِجَكُم", l: "أَخْرَجَ", lc: 99, tl: "yukh'rijakum", lb: "বের করে আনা",e: "drive you out", b: "তোমাদেরকে বের করে দিতে চায়", i: "mengeluarkan/mengusir kamu", f: 2, rm: "To go out, go forth, depart, evade/escape/extricate oneself from, to quit/forsake, to rebel, to be foul or obscene, conspicuous, be clear (as in clear sky as opposed to cloudy), to resolve/explain/render, educate/discipline/train well, render a thing of two mixtures (such as two colors, black and white, or to write upon part of a tablet and leave part of it blank), make a thing to be of different kinds, contribute to a thing or cause, make an agreement, extort/extract/produce/elicit, to exclude something or someone, to vent, surpass or excel, outstrip others, be external/extrinsic/objective.", ag: "فعل مضارع صيغة ٤ وضمير متصل ", eg: "Verb Imperfect 4th form and Pronoun suffix ", tag: "V", pos: "V", att: "IMPF", qual: "(IV)", deg: "3", gen: "M", num: "S", mood: "SUBJ", lu: "أَخْرَجَ،مُخْرِجٌۭ"},
"26:35:4" : {s: 26, a: 35, w: 4, r: "", t: "مِّنْ", l: "مِن", lc: 3067, tl: "min", lb: "মধ্য থেকে, কিছুর চেয়ে",e: "from", b: "হতে", i: "dari", f: 149, rm: "", ag: "حرف جر ", eg: "Preposition ", tag: "PP", pos: "PP", att: "", qual: "", deg: "", gen: "", num: "", mood: "", lu: ""},
"26:35:5" : {s: 26, a: 35, w: 5, r: "ارض", t: "أَرْضِكُم", l: "أَرْض", lc: 461, tl: "arḍikum", lb: "পৃথিবী",e: "your land", b: "তোমাদের ভুমি", i: "bumimu/negerimu", f: 2, rm: "To rotate, bring forth herbs abundantly. Land abundant, fruitful, productive, luxuriant with herbage. Place for alighting or abiding. To tarry, await, expect, be patient. Earth, as opposed to heaven: and the ground, as meaning the surface of the earth, on which we tread, and sit, and lie. Good land. Remain, fixed, tarry in expectation [on the ground]. Heavy, slow, sluggish, inclining, or propending to the ground. Submissive. A carpet, anything that is spread. A tremor, vertigo arising from a relaxed state. Wood-fretter, termite.", ag: "أسم مجرور وضمير متصل ", eg: "Noun Genitive case and Pronoun suffix ", tag: "N", pos: "N", att: "GEN", qual: "", deg: "", gen: "F", num: "", mood: "", lu: "أَرْضُ"},
